ZH: 我感到绝望，因为我无法达到我的目标。
EN: I feel despair because I cannot reach my goals.

ZH: 她在生活中感到绝望，因为她失去了亲人。
EN: She feels despair in life because she has lost loved ones.

ZH: 当我听到这个坏消息时，我的心情变得绝望。
EN: My mood turned desperate when I heard the bad news.

ZH: 这个困境让我感到绝望，我不知道该怎么办了。
EN: This predicament makes me feel hopeless, I don't know what to do.

ZH: 他的绝望使他陷入了深深的悲伤之中。
EN: His despair plunged him into deep sadness.

ZH: 考试失败之后，他感到绝望和失望。
EN: After failing the exam, he felt despair and disappointment.

ZH: 她的绝望情绪让人难过。
EN: Her desperate mood is heartbreaking.

ZH: 经历了一系列挫折后，他对未来感到绝望。
EN: After a series of setbacks, he feels despair about the future.

ZH: 这个困难的挑战让他心生绝望。
EN: This difficult challenge leaves him in despair.

ZH: 当他失去了工作时，他感到了前所未有的绝望。
EN: When he lost his job, he felt an unprecedented despair.

ZH: 这个失去亲人的悲剧使她陷入了深深的绝望之中。
EN: The tragedy of losing loved ones plunged her into deep despair.

ZH: 无尽的绝望感笼罩着整个城市。
EN: Endless despair hangs over the entire city.

ZH: 尽管遭受了失败和挫折，他不曾感到绝望。
EN: Despite experiencing failure and setbacks, he never felt despair.

ZH: 只有继续努力，我们才能摆脱绝望的局面。
EN: Only by persevering can we overcome the situation of despair.

ZH: 她的绝望使她无法集中精力。
EN: Her despair makes it difficult for her to concentrate.

ZH: 面对一切困难，她依然保持着希望，而非绝望。
EN: In the face of all difficulties, she still maintains hope instead of despair.

ZH: 这个困境使他感到绝望，他急需帮助。
EN: This predicament makes him feel hopeless, he desperately needs help.

ZH: 对未来的不确定性使她感到了绝望。
EN: The uncertainty of the future has filled her with despair.

ZH: 我们不能对失败感到绝望，应该坚持下去。
EN: We should not feel despair from failure, we should persevere.

ZH: 他成功地战胜了自己的绝望和困难。
EN: He successfully overcame his own despair and difficulties.
